.TH QDSPLIT 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qdsplit \- split a querydata file into per-time-step files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qdsplit
.RI [ options ]
.I inputfile outputdir
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qdsplit
splits each time step in the input querydata into a separate file in
the output directory. This is useful for assembling rolling forecast
archives where each time step is stored individually.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print the help message.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode.
.TP
.B \-s
Use short filenames.
.TP
.BI \-t " n"
Number of time steps to process simultaneously (default 1).
.TP
.BI \-T " n"
As
.B \-t
but use memory-mapped output.
.TP
.BI \-m " percent"
How much data is allowed to be missing before the time step is
discarded, in percent (default 100).
.TP
.B \-O
Set the origin time equal to the valid time in the resulting files.
.SH EXAMPLES
Split a forecast file into per-hour files:
.PP
.RS 4
qdsplit forecast.sqd /data/forecast/by_time
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qdcombine (1),
.BR combineHistory (1),
.BR qdcrop (1)
